docs.abstract: It’s not the first self-driving bike. But equipped with an A.I. chip, it may be the nearest to thinking for itself.
docs.snippet: It’s not the first self-driving bike. But equipped with an A.I. chip, it may be the nearest to thinking for itself.
docs.lead_paragraph: As corporate giants like Ford, G.M. and Waymo struggle to get their self-driving cars on the road, a team of researchers in China is rethinking autonomous transportation using a souped-up bicycle.

headline.main: And Now, a Bicycle Built for None
headline.print_headline: Self-Driving Bike Glides Toward the Future of A.I.

docs.abstract: With the acquisition of a leading business software company, IBM is presenting itself as an open, impartial player in the cloud computing industry.
docs.snippet: With the acquisition of a leading business software company, IBM is presenting itself as an open, impartial player in the cloud computing industry.
docs.lead_paragraph: IBM has tried multiple ways to stay relevant in the technology world. But it has often been outgunned by rivals like Amazon and Microsoft.

headline.main: IBM Bets $34 Billion That Red Hat Can Help It Catch Amazon and Microsoft
headline.print_headline: IBM Wagers  $34 Billion  On Red Hat

docs.abstract: The hospital technology, typically used to identify human ailments, captured perhaps the world’s smallest magnetic resonance image.
docs.snippet: The hospital technology, typically used to identify human ailments, captured perhaps the world’s smallest magnetic resonance image.
docs.lead_paragraph: As our devices get smaller and more sophisticated, so do the materials we use to make them. That means we have to get up close to engineer new materials. Really close.

headline.main: Scientists Took an M.R.I. Scan of an Atom
headline.print_headline: Tiny Details: Putting an Atom Through the M.R.I. Machine
